crops.presented_by: Dr. J. Dufrenoy
crops.institution_involved: Station de Pathologie Vegetale, Pont de la Maye, Gironde
crops.description: A hardy perennial, grown in the Pyrenees, but originally from Liberia.

crops.presented_by: Robert M. Grey, Superintendent
crops.institution_involved: Atkins Institution of the Arnold Arboretum. Soledad, Cienfuegos
crops.description: An erect shrub or small tree which has obtusely lobed leathery leaves, broader than long, and few-flowered clusters of pure yellow flowers. It is native to India. For previous introduction see 98802.

crops.presented_by: the McGregor Museum, Kimberley
crops.institution_involved: McGregor Museum, Kimberley
crops.description: A strongly resin-scented shrub, native to southern Africa, with oblong to obovate, entire leaves up to 2 inches long and short racemes of small woolly flower heads. It is said to be a good stock feed and to be drought resistant. For previous introduction see 98012.

crops.presented_by: the forest botanist
crops.institution_involved: Forest Research Institute, Dehra Dun, United Provinces
crops.description: A South African bulbous plant with six to nine linear-subulate, channeled, hairy leaves a foot long and green yellow-margined flowers in a lax raceme on a scape as long as the leaves.

crops.presented_by: the forest botanist
crops.institution_involved: Forest Research Institute, Dehra Dun, United Provinces
crops.description: A handsome tropical tree, native to Malaya, with ovate-oblong acute leaves and very numerous pale-rose flowers in much-branched terminal panicles. Larger in all parts than Lagerstroemia indica.

crops.presented_by: the forest botanist
crops.institution_involved: Forest Research Institute, Dehra Dun, United Provinces
crops.description: A tall tropical tree 70 to 100 feet high, with elliptic-lanceolate leaves 3 to 6 inches long, hairy beneath, and purple flowers in axillary and terminal panicles. Native to Burma. Much larger than Lagerstroemia indica, but with less showy flowers.

crops.presented_by: the forest botanist
crops.institution_involved: Forest Research Institute, Dehra Dun, United Provinces
crops.description: A tropical banana relative about 12 feet high, with leaves 7 feet long and fruits 4 inches long. For previous introduction see 75282.

crops.presented_by: the forest botanist
crops.institution_involved: Forest Research Institute, Dehra Dun, United Provinces
crops.description: A bulbous perennial 12 to 18 inches high, native to India and tropical America. The flower scape, appearing before the linear leaves, bears a raceme 6 to 12 inches long of drooping campanulate flowers an inch long, greenish white with green nerves. For previous introduction see 103630.

crops.presented_by: the forest botanist
crops.institution_involved: Forest Research Institute, Dehra Dun, United Provinces
crops.description: A bulbous plant, unknown except in cultivation, with linear bright-green leaves a foot long and bright-yellow, red, or white flowers over an inch long on scapes about 5 inches high. For previous introduction see 68125.
